<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-87-1268 </DOCNO><TEXT>The heat supply system of a medium-size industrial establishment was convertedto steam generated in and supplied from various sources. At the sametime heavy oil and light oil were replaced by natural gas. Measurementsmade before and after retrofitting showed substantial savings in energyconsumption and a distinct reduction in pollutant discharges.</TEXT></DOC>